Put a large #saucepan{} of water with a pinch of @salt{pinch} on to boil for the
wheat pasta. Put a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil!). When hot, add the
@lamb mince{200%g}, break it up with a #wooden spoon{} and cook until well
browned, about ~{5%minutes}. Drain off any excess fat.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).
Pick the @rosemary{1/2}(finely chopped) leaves from their stalks and discard the
stalks. Add the onion, garlic and half the rosemary to the lamb. Give it a stir
and lower the heat to medium. Cook until the onion has softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> TIP: Rosemary is a strongly flavoured herb so add less if you're not a huge fan.

When the water is boiling, stir in the @rigatoni pasta{200%g}. Cook for
~{11%minutes}. When cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pot off the
heat. Drizzle on some @olive oil{} to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, add the @tomato passata{1}, @chicken stock powder{1/2}, @water{150%ml}
to the frying pan. Bring to the boil and stir to dissolve the stock powder.
Reduce the heat to a simmer and let the sauce thicken and reduce by half,
~{15%minutes}. Add the @baby spinach{125%g}, stir through, and cook until wilted.
Preheat your #grill{} to its highest setting.

In a #small bowl{}, mix the remaining rosemary with half the @Italian style
grated hard cheese{} and all of the @panko breadcrumbs{18.75%g}. Season with
@salt{} and @black pepper{} and stir in a glug of @olive oil{}.

> TIP: You want the breadcrumbs to go golden brown but not burn, so watch them closely!

Mix the @reduced fat creme fraiche{112.5%g} and remaining cheese into the pasta.
Spoon your lamb mixture into an #ovenproof dish{} and top with the creamy pasta.
Sprinkle the breadcrumbs on top and grill for ~{2-3%minutes}. Serve immediately.
Enjoy!